      "content": "oh my bad, i meant the general trend of the proposed changes being debated right now since the 2017 stuff is expiring soon. basically, if they go ahead with the big tax hikes on corporations and high earners to fund social programs, how does that actually affect inequality according to the experts? is there a consensus on whether that works or if it just kills growth?",
